Notes:
and i responded to him:
Hi Mike – we would love to have you join the wonderful folks in Tallahassee!

We are not much of an industrial town – Our biggest employers are the State of Florida and the universities:  Florida State University (FSU), Florida Agricultural and Mechanical University (FAMU), and Tallahassee Community College (TCC).

We do have some companies like General Dynamics and an ammunitions plant 15 miles south of Tallahassee in St. Marks.  And we have the companies that provide goods and services to the entities listed above.

As for the health care in the area – we are blessed with two hospitals:  Tallahassee Regional (public)  and Capital Regional (private)  they are fiercely competitive – each bragging on different areas of expertise.  The links to each are below so you can search for those treatments of interest to you.  

I hope Tallahassee will interest you enough for a visit – this is a lovely southern town with Spanish Moss hanging in the large old oak trees draping over lovely winding roads.  The people are friendly and your money tends to go farther here than northeast states. I have also included the link to a very informative school site that can help you evaluate the local schools, or any others in the greater SE.

I will be happy to give you a tour of Tallahassee if you decide to come for a visit.

Best wishes,

Eva

List of websites below:  Schools, public hospital, private hospital and economic development council list of major employers----

www.greatschools.org
https://www.tmh.org/ (Tallahassee Memorial Hospital – the really large public hospital)
http://capitalregionalmedicalcenter.com/our-services/
http://taledc.com/major-employers/

I guess what I am saying is we aren't very diverse in that respect so an area with multiple industries would be a plus.

Once we examine some of the important things on our list we will start honing in on a geographic area.

-Mike
